[h3 id=Comments
 
	" Comments
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"The game has a in-built autofire detector and prevent you from using brute button mashing. This leads to a more subtile mashing
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Stagebystagecomments
 
	" Stage by stage comments
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=100m
 
	" 100m
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Pure speed. Forward leaning is useless.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Longjump.
 
	" Long jump.
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Jump as late as possible, with optimum angle of 47 degrees. Continue to mash in the air. Foul is the fastest for the two last attempts.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=ShotPut
 
	" Shot Put
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Throw as late as possible with an angle of 41 degrees. Stop mashing to accelerate as late as possible. Continue to mash in the air. Foul is the fastest for the two last attempts.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=100mFreeStyle
 
	" 100m Free Style
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Mashing buttons until turn. The best turn is frame perfect and avoid decreasing the speed.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=110mHurdle
 
	" 110m Hurdle
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Mashing the button while jumping relatively early for each hurdle. Forward leaning is usefull for finish.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=HighJump
 
	" High Jump
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"First jump is to set the proper height, the second is the world record. Last one is the fastest possible foul.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Hammer
 
	" Hammer
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Release the hammer as late as possible, avoid mashing for 3 frames to sync the release with the latest moment before foul. Two last attempts are foul.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=TripleJump
 
	" Triple Jump
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Only the last jump make the performance. Push X as late as possible with an angle of 45 degrees.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Javelin
 
	" Javelin
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Best angle is 44 degrees, continue to mash while in the air.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=PoleVault
 
	" Pole Vault
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"First jump sets the altitude as high as possible. Second jump is the world record. It requires to jump it backward. Last jump is a fast foul.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Discus
 
	" Discus
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Avoid mashing for 2 frames to throw it as close as possible to the line.
	$LF
]p
